data.name: Flytac 120 - 90W
data.description: Flytac 120 - 90W is a granular, water-white, modified gum rosin polyols esters made from specially refined gum rosin using a series of advanced processes of partial hydrogenation, esterification, and stabilization. They are a new generation of natural tackifier resins that exhibit good aging resistance, and excellent compatibility. Also capable of raising the initial and persistent viscosity of pressure-sensitive adhesive in a simultaneous way, the excellent heat stability increases by less than 1 degree of Gardner Color within consecutive 8 hours at 180°C.

data.name: Dragonox® PDP
data.description: Dragonox® PDP is a liquid-type antioxidant with good color and heat stability. This product is widely used in polyvinyl chloride (PVC), acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS), polyurethanes (PU), polycarbonates (PC), and coatings.

data.name: Dragonsorb® 3039
data.description: Dragonsorb® 3039 is a liquid UV absorber with a stable morphology. It has good compatibility with all common plasticizers. This product is especially suitable for the stabilizers of PVC-P and PVC plastisol. It can also be used in polyurethane (PUR), polyester, polymethacrylate (PMMA), and other materials to improve the weatherability of the materials under UV conditions.

data.name: Flytac 103 - E

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Glycerol ester of disproportionated rosin, Glycerol ester of wood rosin

data.description:
Flytac 103 - E is a slightly yellow, transparent solid made from gum rosin through esterification with glycerol. This product has a high viscosity, low VOC, excellent heat and aging stability, excellent polymer compatibility, etc.
Typical Uses

EVA, SBS, SIS, and other hot melt adhesives due to their stability and excellent polymer compatibility.
It can also be used in construction adhesives, rubber compounding, sealants, coatings, and other applications.

data.name: Flyadd® AY1
data.description: Flyadd® AY1 is a color stabilizer and anti-yellowing agent. It is used as a polymer additive for polyurethane and is a highly effective additive for many kinds of dispersed polymer systems. This product has the potential to improve color and heat stability in processing and end applications.

data.name: Dragonox® 1135
data.description: Dragonox® 1135 is an excellent antioxidant that may be used in a variety of polymers. Because of its low volatility and excellent compatibility, it is particularly well suited for use in forced air cooling processes for PU. This product is used in the stabilization of PV flexible slabstock foams to prevent the formation of peroxides in the polyol during storage and transport and to further protect against scorching during foaming. It also helps prevent fogging in automotive applications, and the low volatility of this product makes it a perfect fit where meat liquids, emulsions, suspensions, solutions, or melts are an integral part of polymer manufacturing and processing. This product has the convenience of a pumpable liquid that can be added before, during, or after polymerization.

data.name: Dragonox® 1315
data.description: Dragonox® 1315 is a low-viscosity liquid-type antioxidant. Due to its alkyl chain, this product has a broad compatibility range and is soluble in various substances. It is an excellent antioxidant for polymers (such as PVC, ABS, etc.), lubricating oil, and polyurethane foam.

data.name: Flytac 102
data.description:
Flytac 102 is a slightly yellow, transparent solid made from gum rosin through esterification with pentaerythritol. This product has a high viscosity, low VOC, excellent heat and aging stability, excellent polymer compatibility, etc.
Typical Uses

EVA base hot melt glue sticks
Bookbinding
Pressure-sensitive adhesive based on SIS or SBS adhesive
Emulsion and paints based on NR and CR

data.name: Flytac 120 (Water White Rosin Ester)
data.description: Flytac 120 is a granular, water-white, modified gum rosin polyols esters made from specially refined gum rosin using a series of advanced processes of partial hydrogenation, esterification, and stabilization. They are a new generation of natural tackifier resins that exhibit good aging resistance, and excellent compatibility. Also capable of raising the initial and persistent viscosity of pressure-sensitive adhesive in a simultaneous way, the excellent heat stability increases by less than 1 degree of Gardner Color within consecutive 8 hours at 180°C.

data.name: Flytac 192
data.description: Flytac 192 is a water-white thermoplastic resin obtained from the polymerization of aromatic and hydrogenation. It is widely applied in hot melt adhesive (HMA), and pressure sensitive adhesive (PSA) because of its good heat resistance and good compatibility with base polymers such as SIS, EVA, SBS, SEBS, and polyolefin. It can also be used in road marking, BOPP masterbatch, and rubber compounding.

data.name: Flytac 190 (Hydrocarbon Resin C9)

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Caustic Soda, NaOH, Soda Lye, Sodium Hydrate, White Caustic

data.description: Flytac 190 is obtained by cracking C9, which mainly contains vinyl toluene, indene, methyl indene, and other unsaturated aromatic compounds. To have the characteristics of both aliphatic and aromatic resins C5 is added in C9, copolymerized, and modified to get C5/C9 copolymer hydrocarbon resin. As a result, this product has improved compatibility with EVA and also has good solubility in various solvents.

data.name: Flytac 189 (Hydrocarbon Resin C9)
data.description: Flytac 189 is made by C9 cracking through catalytic polymerization. This light yellow granular solid has good heat stability, solubility, water resistance, and very good chemical stability over acid and alkali. It is mainly used as fertilizer in paint, rubber, adhesives, printing ink, plastic floor tile, and modified asphalt industries.

data.name: Flytac 111 - 101 (Hydrogenated Rosin)
data.description: Flytac 111 - 101 is a thermoplastic, acidic resin produced by hydrogenating rosin to an exceptionally high degree with eliminated foreign matter and coloring radicals. It is one of the palest, most highly stabilized rosins commercially available. This product is especially indicated as the tackifier in solvent adhesives and hot-melt applied coatings and adhesives that must excel in these properties.

data.name: Flytac 111 - 301 （Water White Hydrogenated Rosin)
data.description: Flytac 111 - 301 is a thermoplastic, acidic resin produced by hydrogenating rosin to an exceptionally high degree with eliminated foreign matter and coloring radicals. It is one of the palest, most highly stabilized rosins commercially available. This product is especially indicated as the tackifier in solvent adhesives and hot-melt applied coatings and adhesives that must excel in these properties.

data.name: Flytac 106 - F (Hydrogenated Pentaerythritol Rosin Ester)
data.description: Flytac 106 - F is a medium hard, pale thermoplastic resin designed primarily as a tackifier for various types of polymer and elastomer-based adhesives. It is a pentaerythritol ester of a rosin that has been stabilized by hydrogenation. In adhesive formulations, it contributes improved resistance to oxidation, greater heat stability, better retention of color, and greater retention of tack-imparting properties than ordinary rosin ester resins. For cosmetic applications such as mascara, the INCI name for Pentalyn H-E is Pentaerythrityl Hydrogenated Rosinate.

It is a pentaerythritol ester of a rosin that has been stabilized by hydrogenation. In adhesive formulations, it contributes improved resistance to oxidation, greater heat stability, better retention of color, and greater retention of tack-imparting properties than ordinary rosin ester resins. For cosmetic applications such as mascara, the INCI name for Pentalyn H-E is Pentaerythrityl Hydrogenated Rosinate.

items: (2Z)-2-Butenedioic acid, (2Z)-Butene-2-dioic acid, (Z)-2-Butenedioic acid, 2-Butenedioic acid (2Z)-, 2-Butenedioic acid (Z)-, cis-1,2-Ethylenedicarboxylic acid, cis-2-Butenedioic acid, cis-Butenedioic acid, Maleinic acid, Malezid CM, Toxilic acid

data.description: Flytac 114 is a slightly yellow transparent solid obtained by the esterification of gum rosin and maleic anhydride using glycerol or pentaerythritol. This product is soluble in coal tars, esters, and turpentine oil, insoluble in alcoholic solvents, partially soluble in petroleum solvents, and soluble well in plant oils. It has the advantages of stable color, resistance to yellowing, good heat resistance, and adhesion.

data.name: Flytac 188
data.description: Flytac 188 is a light yellow aliphatic hydrocarbon resin. It is polymerized by high-purity 1.3-pentadiene and designed as a tackifier in hot melt/pressure-sensitive adhesives. This product has good heat resistance, light odor, and good compatibility with polymers like SBS, SIS, SEBS, EVA, SBR, NR, and polyisobutylene.

data.name: Flytac 191 (Hydrogenated C5 Resin)
data.description: Flytac 191’s is obtained by hydrogenating cracked C5 to achieve high-quality, multi-purpose, water-white thermoplastic hydrocarbon resin. This C5 hydrogenated hydrocarbon resin is mainly used for hot melt adhesives, and hot melt pressure sensitive adhesive tackifiers. It has good thermal stability, low odor, and good compatibility with SIS, APAO, etc.
